# cognitive-claude / .gitignore
#
# This repo ships a framework. The framework, when installed, produces
# operator-local artifacts (telemetry logs, calibration history, session
# states). None of those belong in the repo. This file prevents them
# from being accidentally committed if an operator runs the system from
# inside the cloned tree.

# Operator-local runtime artifacts (HANDBOOK §4, §5)
.session-state.md
.session-state.*
.session-todo.md
*.session-state.md

# Telemetry / calibration history (if a contributor symlinks the repo
# into their ~/.claude/ for testing and runtime data leaks back in)
telemetry/
bridge-history.jsonl
audit-history.jsonl
last-boot-status.txt

# Operator-local evidence packs (CASE_STUDY canonical pack stays;
# personal evidence stays out)
my-evidence.json
*-evidence.json
!examples/**/EVIDENCE.json

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# Python bytecode (cost-audit.py + stress-test.py are stdlib only and
# should never produce __pycache__ if invoked via `python3 file.py`,
# but defense-in-depth)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Backups (operator backups go to ~/.claude/.backups/ by INSTALL_PROMPT
# convention, not into the repo, but defense-in-depth)
*.bak
*.backup
.backups/
